Subject: [PATCH 11/18] =?UTF-8?q?inline-3d(#625):=20plumb=20inline=5F3d=5F?=
 =?UTF-8?q?rects=20through=20LayerContext=20=E2=80=94=20retire=20--disable?=
 =?UTF-8?q?-features=3DTreesInViz?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Chrome's default TreesInVizInClientProcess() forwards each frame to Viz as a
LayerContext display-tree update (LayerTreeUpdate) that carried latency_info +
tracked_element_rects but NOT the DisplayXR inline_3d_rects. On the Viz side
MakeCompositorFrameMetadata then rebuilt metadata with an empty inline_3d_rects
(active_tree()->inline_3d_rects() is never populated on the Viz tree), so
MaybeWeaveOutput saw no rects and never wove. The B4b launch worked around this
with --disable-features=TreesInViz.

Fix: carry inline_3d_rects through the display-tree update, mirroring
tracked_element_rects exactly:
 - mojom LayerTreeUpdate gains array<gfx.mojom.Rect> inline_3d_rects.
 - LayerContext::UpdateDisplayTreeFrom (+ base virtual, viz/fake/test impls)
   and LayerTreeHostImpl::UpdateDisplayTree gain the param; the client threads
   compositor_frame.metadata.inline_3d_rects into it.
 - LayerContextImpl applies it via a new
   LayerTreeHostImpl::set_inline_3d_rects_from_client / _from_client_ member.
 - MakeCompositorFrameMetadata sets metadata.inline_3d_rects from the client
   copy in the trees_in_viz_in_viz_process branch (and from active_tree() in the
   renderer-side branch), matching tracked_element_rects.

Validated in real chrome with --disable-features=TreesInViz REMOVED: the weave
fires end-to-end (service leia_dp_d3d11_process_atlas weave: target=2593x1974
vp=(374,920 1810x1054), zero OpenSharedResource 0x80070057) and the inline canvas
is glasses-free 3D (user eyeball).

